---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import BadgeComp from '../../components/Badge.astro';
import ComponentDocsSections from '../../components/ComponentDocsSections.astro';

const usageSnippet = `---\nimport { Badge } from 'comet-astro';\n\n---\n\n<Badge label="Launch ready" variant="success" />`;
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Badge"
  description="Compact status label with AAA contrast across light and dark mode."
>
  <ComponentDocsSections
    overview={
      <fragment>
        <p>Badges call out short states or categories without overpowering surrounding copy. Each variant uses a high-contrast palette that meets WCAG AAA for small text in both themes, so the label remains legible even inside dense tables or cards.</p>
        <p>Drop badges inline with headings, lists, or buttons. Prefix a status, highlight an availability window, or draw attention to experimental features without introducing a full alert.</p>
      </fragment>
    }
    props={
      <fragment>
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-800 rounded-md overflow-hidden">
          <thead class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800">
            <tr>
              <th class="p-2 text-left">Prop</th>
              <th class="p-2 text-left">Type</th>
              <th class="p-2 text-left">Default</th>
              <th class="p-2 text-left">Description</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr class="border-t border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-800">
              <td class="p-2 font-mono">label</td>
              <td class="p-2 font-mono">string</td>
              <td class="p-2 font-mono">—</td>
              <td class="p-2">Text content of the badge. Keep it brief—typically a single word or short phrase.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-t border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-800">
              <td class="p-2 font-mono">variant</td>
              <td class="p-2 font-mono">'neutral' | 'primary' | 'success' | 'warning' | 'danger'</td>
              <td class="p-2 font-mono">'neutral'</td>
              <td class="p-2">Visual theme for the badge.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-t border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-800">
              <td class="p-2 font-mono">className</td>
              <td class="p-2 font-mono">string</td>
              <td class="p-2 font-mono">''</td>
              <td class="p-2">Additional utility classes to append.</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </fragment>
    }
    accessibility={
      <fragment>
        <p>AAA contrast is built in: we target at least a 9:1 ratio between background and text in both themes. Because badges often appear next to other interactive controls, keeping them readable helps everyone parse statuses quickly.</p>
        <p>The component renders a plain <code>span</code>, so no extra ARIA roles are required. Ensure the label string itself is localised for assistive technology users.</p>
      </fragment>
    }
    theming={
      <fragment>
        <p>Badge palettes are tokenized; override via custom utility classes or CSS variables if integrating into a broader design system. Maintain ≥ 7:1 contrast for the small text size. Prefer deep backgrounds (950 range) for light mode and light backgrounds (100 range) for dark mode to keep semantic color mapping intuitive.</p>
      </fragment>
    }
    examples={
      <fragment>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3">
          <BadgeComp label="Neutral" variant="neutral" />
          <BadgeComp label="Primary" variant="primary" />
          <BadgeComp label="Success" variant="success" />
          <BadgeComp label="Warning" variant="warning" />
          <BadgeComp label="Danger" variant="danger" />
        </div>
        <p class="text-xs text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-400">Each variant pairs a deep tone in light mode with a light counterpart in dark mode, ensuring the 12px text remains legible everywhere.</p>
        <h3 class="mt-6 text-base font-semibold">Inline usage</h3>
        <p>Add a badge to release notes or API titles to call out lifecycle information.</p>
  <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold">v3.1 Launch Notes <BadgeComp label="Stable" variant="success" className="ml-2" /></h4>
        <h3 class="mt-6 text-base font-semibold">Grouped legend</h3>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2">
          <BadgeComp label="Alpha" variant="warning" />
          <BadgeComp label="Live" variant="primary" />
          <BadgeComp label="Limited" variant="danger" />
        </div>
      </fragment>
    }
    interactive={
      <fragment>
        <p>Usage:</p>
        <pre class="overflow-x-auto rounded-lg border border-neutral-300 dark:border-neutral-700 bg-neutral-950/80 p-4 text-xs text-neutral-50"><code class="language-astro">{usageSnippet}</code></pre>
      </fragment>
    }
  />
</DocsLayout>
